name: “Old One Eye”
text: [REACTION]: After this warlord readies, remove half the damage from it. (Limit once per round.)

name: Lurking Hormagaunt
text: [REACTION]: After this unit is assigned damage, reassign up to 2 of that damage to your warlord instead.

name: Awakening Cavern
text: [ACTION]: Exhaust this support to ready a target unit you control.
flavor: Isolated from the Hive Mind and frozen in the ice-packs of Calth, mindless killers lurk, waiting to be unleashed.

name: Ferocious Strength
text: [ACTION]: Your warlord or a synapse unit you control gains Brutal until the end of the combat round.
flavor: Old One Eye's destructive power has no bounds.

name: Great Scything Talons
text:
Attach to your warlord.
Attached unit gets +1 HP.
[REACTION]: After damage is removed from attached unit, it gets +X ATK for its next attack this phase. X is the amount of damage removed.

name: “The Swarmlord”
text: [REACTION]: After this warlord commits to a planet, put 1 Termagant token into play at each adjacent planet.

name: Brood Warriors
text: [HIVE MIND] - Each Termagant token you control at this planet gains 1 command icon.
flavor: Tyranid Warriors act as links in the synaptic web of the Hive Mind, issuing commands to lesser bioforms.

name: Leviathan Hive Ship
text: [REACTION]: After a unit you control with the Hive Mind specialization and printed cost 3 or lower is destroyed, exhaust this support to put that unit into play from you discard pile exhausted at a planet.

name: Indescribable Horror
text: [COMBAT ACTION]: Rout a target army unit with printed cost equal to or lower than the number of [TYRANID] units you control at that planet.

name: Bone Sabres
text:
Attach to your warlord.
Attached unit gets +1 ATK.
[REACTION]: After attached unit destroys an enemy army unit by an attack, put 1 Termagant token into play at this planet.

name: Savage Warrior Prime
text:
This unit must commit to a different planet than your warlord, if able.
While checking for a battle and determining initiative at this planet, this unit is considered to be a warlord, unless an enemy warlord is at this planet.

name: Blazing Zoanthrope
text: [REACTION]: After the combat phase begins, deal 1 damage to a target army unit at this planet. If this planet is infested, deal 2 damage instead.
flavor: Zoanthropes channel the psychic potential of the Hive Mind into devastating blasts of energy.

name: Gravid Tervigon
text: [REACTION]: After this unit commits to a planet, put 1 Termagant token into play at this planet. If this planet is infested, put 2 Termagant tokens into play at this planet instead.

name: Stalking Lictor
flavor: Lictors are the spies and assassins of the Tyranids, able to infiltrate enemy territory ahead of the swarm and discover the location of enemy forces by devouring the brains of its foes.

name: Venomthrope Polluter
text: [REACTION]: After this unit commits to a planet, move a non-warlord unit you control from the planet with your warlord to this planet.

name: Ripper Swarm
flavor: Ripper Swarms are used to scour a planet of its resources, devouring bio-mass indiscriminately until nothing is left.

name: Strangler Brood
text: [HIVE MIND] - Each Termagant token you control at this planet gets +1 ATK.
flavor: A Tyranid armed with a barbed strangler is a force to be reckoned with, launching hooked tendrils that tear apart both flesh and armor.

name: Termagant Sentry
text: [REACTION]: After a Termagant token you control is destroyed at this planet, ready this unit.
flavor: Termagants wander the arterial passages of a bio-ship, ever at the ready in case of intruders.

name: Hunter Gargoyles
text: [COMBAT ACTION]: Move this unit to an infest planet. (Limit once per phase.)
flavor: Tyranid Gargoyles incite terror in enemy ranks, keeping them disoriented until it is far too late.

name: Virulent Spore Sacs
text: [COMBAT ACTION]: Sacrifice this unit to deal 1 damage to each enemy unit at this planet and infest this plant.

name: Scything Hormagaunts
text: [REACTION]: After you deploy this unit, infest this planet.
flavor: In the initial stages of a Tyranid invasion Hormagaunts are dropped by the millions, weakening the planet's defenses with waves of vicious talons.

name: Toxic Venomthrope
text: [REACTION]: After you win a command struggle at this planet, infest it. If it was already infested, either gain 1 [RESOURCE] or draw 1 card instead of infesting it.

name: Termagant Horde
text: [REACTION]: After a combat round at this planet begins, put 1 Termagant token into play at this planet.
flavor: You never see just one Termagant...

name: Volatile Pyrovore
text: [INTERRUPT]: When this unit is destroyed by an attack, deal 3 damage to the attacker.
flavor: Upon its death, the unstable ichors contained within the stomach of a Pyrovore may ignite, causing an explosion that consumes anything around it.

name: Termagant Spikers
text: [HIVE MIND] - Each Termagant token you control at this planet gains Ranged.

name: Tyranid Warrior
flavor: Tyranid Warriors are unstoppable killing machines with pulsing ichor for blood, needle-sharp teeth, and darkly gleaming eyes that reveal a terrible intelligence.

name: Swarm Guard
text: [HIVE MIND] - Each Termagant token you control at this planet gets +2 HP.
flavor: These creatures are built like living shields and can shrugg off wounds that would blow a man apart.

name: Adamant Hive Guard
text: [REACTION]: After a unit with the Hive Mind specialization or Termagant token at this planet is assigned damage, reassign all of that damage to this unit instead.

name: Ymgarl Genestealer
text:
This unit gets +2 HP while it is at a planet with a synapse unit.
This unit gets +2 ATK while it is at a planet with a warlord.

name: Ravenous Haruspex
text: [REACTION]: After this unit destroys an enemy army unit by an attack, gain X [RESOURCE]. X is equal to the printed cost of the destroyed unit. (Limit once per phase.)

name: Biovore Spore Launcher
text: [HIVE MIND] - Each Termagant token you control at this planet gains Area Effect (1).

name: Shrieking Harpy
text: [COMBAT ACTION]: After this unit is declared as an attacker at an infested planet, exhaust each enemy non-Elite army unit and token unit at this planet.

name: Burrowing Trygon
text: Reduce the cost to deploy this unit by X. X is the highest number of Termagant tokens you control at a single planet.

name: Clogged with Corpses
text: [ACTION]: Sacrifice X Termagant units to destroy a target support card with printed cost X or lower.
flavor: Termagants are highly expendable and the Hive Mind has no qualms about burying a foe in the bodies of its fallen.

name: Predation
text: [ACTION]: Infest a planet adjacent to an infested planet.
flavor: “We have given the horror a name to salve our fears; we call it the Tyranid race, but if it is aware of us at all, it must know us only as Prey.” -Inquisitor Czevak

name: Spawn Termagants
text: [DEPLOY ACTION]: Put 1 Termagant token into play at each planet.
flavor: “When you fight Tyranids you face not only those before you on the field of battle, but the untold thousands which seek to surround you.” -Marneus Calgar

name: Spore Burst
text: [DEPLOY ACTION]: Put a unit with printed cost 3 or lower into play from your discard pile at an infested planet.

name: Dark Cunning
text: [COMBAT ACTION]: Ready a target non-warlord unit you control. Then, if that unit is at an infested planet, gain 1 [RESOURCE]

name: Consumption
text: [DEPLOY ACTION]: Each player must sacrifice a unit at each planet, if able.
flavor: “We must scour them from the stars, before they do the same to us.” -Chaplain Ortan Cassius

name: Regeneration
text:
Attach to an army unit.
Limit 1 per unit.
Attached unit gets +2 HP.
[ACTION]: Exhaust this attachment to remove 2 damage from attached unit.

name: Noxious Fleshborer
text:
Attach to an army unit.
Attached unit gets +1 ATK and +1 HP while it is at an infested planet.
[REACTION]: After you win a command struggle at this planet, infest it.

name: Pincer Tail
text:
Attach to an army unit.
Attached unit gets +1 ATK.
[REACTION]: After attached unit damages an enemy non-warlord unit by an attack, the damaged unit cannot retreat before the start of the next combat round.

name: Parasitic Infection
text:
Attach to an enemy army unit.
[REACTION]: After the combat phase begins, put 1 Termagant token into play at this planet and deal attached unit 1 damage.

name: Heavy Venom Cannon
text:
Attach to an Elite army unit.
Attached unit gets +2 ATK.
[COMBAT ACTION]: Attached unit, until the end of the phase, gain either (choose one): Area Effect (2) or Armorbane. (Limit once per phase.)

name: Brood Chamber
text: [COMBAT ACTION]: Exhaust this support to give a target army unit you control a keyword (and all associated values) printed on a target enemy unit at that planet until the end of the phase.

name: Digestion Pool
text: [INTERRUPT]: When you deploy a [TYRANID] unit at an infested planet, exhaust this support to reduce the unit's cost by 2.

name: Mycetic Spores
text: [COMBAT ACTION]: Exhaust this support to move a unit you control with the Hive Mind specialization to a planet with a Termagant token.

name: Spore Chimney
text: [REACTION]: After the headquarters phase begins, infest a target planet.
flavor: Tyranid Spore Chimneys belch out alien spores that both poison the air and mutate the local fauna.

name: Synaptic Link
text: [REACTION]: After a synapse unit you control commits to a planet, draw 1 card.
flavor: The will of the Hive Mind is channeled through Tyranid commanders to the rest of the swarm, suppressing their animalistic instincts.

name: Veteran Barbrus
text: [REACTION]: After this unit enters play, deal 2 damage to a target army unit at this planet. This ability cannot target [SPACE MARINE], [ASTRA MILITARUM], or [CHAOS] units.

name: Vengeance!
text: [REACTION]: After a unit you control is destroyed by an attack, ready a target [SPACE MARINE] army unit you control at that planet.

name: Seraphim Superior Allegra
text: [REACTION]: After this unit is declared as an attacker, ready a target support card you control.
flavor: “The light of the Emperor guides my hand and my foes shall tremble before His might.” -Seraphim Superior Allegra

name: Holy Fusillade
text: [REACTION]: After a combat round begins, exhaust this support to resolve a ranged skirmish at this battle.

name: Boss Zugnog
text: [COMBAT ACTION]: Target up to 2 [ORK] army units you control at this planet. Deal 1 damage to each targeted unit to move them to the first planet. (Limit once per phase.)

name: Ork Landa
text: [COMBAT ACTION]: Exhaust this support to discard the top card of your deck. If it is an [ORK] card with an odd printed cost, your opponent deals X indirect damage among units he controls. X is the printed cost of the discarded card.

name: Roghrax Bloodhand
text: [BLOODTHIRST] - During a combat round in which 1 or more units have been destroyed at this planet, double this unit's ATK.

name: Ecstatic Seizures
text: [ACTION]: Discard each attachment from each unit at a target planet.
flavor: The powers of Slaanesh can wrack a mortal's body with both pain and pleasure simutaneously, causing him to lose all grip on reality.

name: Solarite Avetys
text: [REACTION]: After this unit takes damage by an attack from a non-flying unit, deal 2 damage to the attacker.

name: Dark Possession
text: [ACTION]: As your next Action this phase, you may play an event card in your opponent's discard pile as if it were in your hand. (You pay its costs, choose its targets, and follow all restrictions.)

name: Autarch Celachia
text: [ACTION]: Pay 1 [RESOURCE] to give this unit one of the following keywords until the end of the round (choose one): Area Effect (1), Armorbane, or Mobile. (Limit once per round.)

name: Subdual
text: [ACTION]: Place a target support card or attachment on top of its owner's deck.
flavor: The psychic might of the Eldar brought to bear in the heat of battle is a remarkable sight to behold.

name: Pathfinder Shi Or'es
text: [ACTION]: Discard an attachment on this unit to ready it. (Limit once per phase.)
flavor: “We Pathfinders are called upon to put down our lives for the Greater Good, and we shall do so gladly.” - Pathfinder Shi  Or'es

name: Repair Bay
text: [DEPLOY ACTION]: Exhaust this support to place a Drone or Pilot card from your discard pile on top of your deck.
